Tremblay 2021

Austin McCoy

March 17 2022

Loading the necessary packages

library(readxl)
library(hagis)
library(pander)

Loading in the data from Tremblay et al 2021, (2016-2019 Quebec, Manitoba and Ontario Canada) manuscript

This study is a little different than the rest in that this data was collected via a molecular diagnostic tool for Phytophthora sojae avr genes. This study found the phenotype and genotype of isolates corresponded 99.5% of the time.

We will look at the data in this order: 1) Quebec, 2) Manitoba and 3) Ontario

final_data <- read_excel("pathotype surveys data.xlsx", 
    sheet = "Tremblay 2021")

final_data_QU <- subset(final_data, state_prov == "Quebec")
final_data_MAN <- subset(final_data, state_prov =="Manitoba")
final_data_ONT <- subset(final_data, state_prov =="Ontario")

Quebec

Setting the hagis arguments - Quebec

hagis_args_QU <- list(
  x = final_data_QU,
  
  cutoff = 1, 
  
  control = "rps",
  
  sample = "Isolate",
  
  gene = "Rps",
  
  perc_susc = "Susceptible.1" 
  
)

isolates <- length(unique(final_data_QU$Isolate))
